            >
              <button
                @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
                class="flex items-center justify-between w-full p-4 pb-1 text-left font-medium select-none"
              >
                <span>{word4}</span>
                <svg
                  class="w-5 h-5 duration-300 ease-out text-accent-600 -rotate-[45deg]"
                  :class="{ '-rotate-[45deg]': activeAccordion==id }"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke-width="1.5"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                  ><path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path></svg
                >
              </button>
              <div x-show="activeAccordion==id" x-collapse="">
                <div class="p-4 pt-2 text-accent-600">
                  {definition4}
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <svg
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          class="inline"
          width="20em"
          height="20em"
          viewBox="0 0 32 32"
        >
          <style>
            .word {
              font-size: 3px;
              fill: #ff7a00;
              font-family: "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif;
            }
          </style>
          <line
            x1="1"
            y1="2"
            x2="8"
            y2="2"
            stroke="#ff7a00"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            stroke-linecap="round"></line>
          <line
            x1="1"
            y1="7"
            x2="8"
            y2="7"
            stroke="#ff7a00"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            stroke-linecap="round"></line>
          <line
            x1="1"
            y1="12"
            x2="5"
            y2="12"
            stroke="#ff7a00"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            stroke-linecap="round"></line>
          <path
            d="M 3 15 v 11 h 18 m 8 -8 v -16 h -17"
            stroke="#ff7a00"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            fill="none"
            stroke-linecap="round"></path>
          <text class="word" x="9" y="7">{word1.toLocaleLowerCase()}</text>
          <text class="word" x="6" y="12">{word2.toLocaleLowerCase()}</text>
          <text class="word" x="10" y="17">{word3.toLocaleLowerCase()}</text>
          <text class="word" x="10" y="22">{word4.toLocaleLowerCase()}</text>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <div
        x-data="{ activeAccordion: '', setActiveAccordion(id) { this.activeAccordion = (this.activeAccordion == id) ? '' : id } }"
        class="md:col-span-2 md:w-3/4 mx-auto"
      >
        <p
          class="text-2xl tracking-tight text-center font-medium text-black mb-4"
        >
          Story
        </p>
        <div x-data="{ id: $id('accordion') }" class="text-gray-500 text-left">
          <p class="mb-4">
The old lighthouse keeper, Silas, inhaled deeply. The salt-laced air, redolent of seaweed and distant storms, filled his lungs. He’d spent his entire life on this craggy point, his world defined by the rhythmic pulse of the beam and the ceaseless crashing of waves. He’d even developed a sort of chiasmus in his daily routine: he worked to maintain the light, the light maintained him.
          </p>
          <div
            @click="setActiveAccordion(id)"
            :class="activeAccordion==id ? 'hidden' : ''"
            class="cursor-pointer text-opacity-70 underline hover:text-accent-900"
          >
            [Continue Reading]
          </div>
          <div x-show="activeAccordion==id" x-collapse="">
            <p class="mb-4">
Today, however, the familiar comfort felt like a cage. News had arrived from the mainland. Scientists had discovered a link between the isolated island population and an unusual rate of encephalization. Their brains, it seemed, were growing, evolving at an accelerated pace. Silas felt a strange pressure in his skull, a burgeoning awareness that both thrilled and terrified him.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-4">
The scientists wanted to study them, to poke and prod and analyze. Silas felt a surge of protectiveness for his community, for the simple, unhurried lives they led. He remembered his grandfather, a man of quiet wisdom, who had warned him about the outside world's insatiable curiosity. "They will measure your skull, not your soul," he'd rasped.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-4">
Silas climbed the winding stairs to the lamp room. He looked out at the churning sea, a mirror of the turmoil within him. He had to make a choice. He thought of the children, their bright, inquisitive eyes. Could he deny them the chance to understand their own evolution? But at what cost?
            </p>
            <p>
He had sworn an oath, years ago, to protect the lighthouse, to keep its light burning. Now, he realized, he had to forswear that oath, or at least redefine it. His duty wasn’t just to the physical structure, but to the people it represented. He would find a way to shield them, to safeguard their unique evolution, even if it meant facing the world’s intrusive gaze. He would be their protector, not just the keeper of the light.
            </p>
            <div
              @click="setActiveAccordion('')"
              :class="activeAccordion==id ? '' : 'hidden'"
              class="cursor-pointer text-opacity-70 underline hover:text-accent-900 mt-4"
            >
              [Hide]
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
